1
00:00:49,048 --> 00:00:51,050
JICHEONG MIDDLE SCHOOL

2
00:00:52,510 --> 00:00:55,305
Today, we'll be learning about
the Trolley Dilemma.

3
00:00:57,098 --> 00:00:58,558
Who knows what a "trolley" is?

4
00:00:59,559 --> 00:01:01,061
-What is that?
-Trolley?

5
00:01:01,144 --> 00:01:02,395
-Beats me.
-What is it?

6
00:01:04,689 --> 00:01:07,692
It's a streetcar. Do you recognize it now?

7
00:01:07,776 --> 00:01:10,195
-I've seen that on TV.
-I see.

8
00:01:10,278 --> 00:01:11,488
I saw it in a movie.

9
00:01:11,571 --> 00:01:14,949
This trolley's brakes are broken,

10
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:18,661
and there are five workers
working on the track.

11
00:01:19,412 --> 00:01:22,415
If you do nothing about it,
all five of them will die.

12
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:25,335
But if you pull a lever,

13
00:01:25,418 --> 00:01:28,922
you can change the trolley's course

14
00:01:29,005 --> 00:01:30,548
to a different track.

15
00:01:31,174 --> 00:01:32,175
However,

16
00:01:32,842 --> 00:01:36,346
there's another worker working
on that track as well.

17
00:01:37,639 --> 00:01:39,224
Let's think about this.

18
00:01:39,307 --> 00:01:40,850
If you don't do anything,

19
00:01:40,934 --> 00:01:43,770
the trolley will kill five people.

20
00:01:43,853 --> 00:01:47,816
If you pull the lever
to change its direction,

21
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:50,068
the five workers will survive

22
00:01:50,151 --> 00:01:52,403
but that one worker will die.

23
00:01:55,990 --> 00:01:57,492
What will be your decision?

24
00:01:58,535 --> 00:02:00,703
I'll definitely pull the lever.

25
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:02,205
I'm not sure.

26
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:03,123
Yes?

27
00:02:03,206 --> 00:02:06,668
I would definitely switch the tracks.
It's five to one.

28
00:02:06,751 --> 00:02:10,130
But those five were fated to die.

29
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:13,216
If I pull the lever, that one worker

30
00:02:13,299 --> 00:02:15,301
would suddenly meet their death.

31
00:02:15,885 --> 00:02:17,220
That would haunt me forever.

32
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:19,681
This is giving me a headache.

33
00:02:19,764 --> 00:02:21,391
Do we have to decide?

34
00:02:22,016 --> 00:02:23,351
Then who will?

35
00:02:23,434 --> 00:02:24,769
Not me.

36
00:02:25,395 --> 00:02:26,980
Hey, you can decide.

37
00:02:27,063 --> 00:02:29,440
No. Why should I?

38
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:31,734
There's no right answer to this dilemma.

39
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:33,695
We each have an opinion.

40
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:37,824
All right. Write a paper
about what you would do and why.

41
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:40,493
Then submit it in two weeks.

42
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:46,040
Seung-kyu.

43
00:02:46,124 --> 00:02:46,958
Seung…

44
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:52,922
-Seung…
-Seung-kyu.

45
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:54,424
-Seung-kyu.
-Seung-kyu.

46
00:02:55,091 --> 00:02:56,676
Seung-kyu!

47
00:02:56,759 --> 00:02:58,428
-Seung-kyu!
-Seung-kyu.

48
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:02,307
Please come this way. It's all right.

49
00:03:02,390 --> 00:03:03,600
Help!

50
00:03:03,683 --> 00:03:05,184
Please help.

51
00:03:05,268 --> 00:03:07,061
-Help!
-It's all right.

52
00:03:12,275 --> 00:03:18,031
MURDERER
NAM JOONG-DO

53
00:03:18,615 --> 00:03:20,408
THE BLAME

54
00:03:21,117 --> 00:03:22,243
Good work.

55
00:03:22,327 --> 00:03:23,870
-Good work.
-Good work.

56
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:34,172
This is Nam Joong-do.

57
00:03:36,424 --> 00:03:38,259
Of course, I remember you.

58
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:41,471
Ms. Na Mun-suk, the head
of Taeyang Apartment's resident committee.

59
00:03:41,554 --> 00:03:44,140
Didn't we meet
at the district office last time?

60
00:03:45,183 --> 00:03:46,893
Yes, it really is my personal number.

61
00:03:52,232 --> 00:03:53,483
NEW MESSAGE FROM
SENIOR SECRETARY LEE SANG-HUN

62
00:04:03,117 --> 00:04:06,704
Ji, a medical student and the assailant
of a case in Sinyang-gu

63
00:04:06,788 --> 00:04:10,458
that led to the suicide
of Namgoong, the victim,

64
00:04:10,541 --> 00:04:13,169
committed suicide by jumping
out of his apartment today

65
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:14,963
after his arrest warrant was issued.

66
00:04:15,046 --> 00:04:16,714
-Goodness.
-Assemblyman Nam Joong-do

67
00:04:16,798 --> 00:04:18,883
-of the Daehan Party…
-No way.

68
00:04:18,967 --> 00:04:21,010
-…had mentioned him to the media recently.
-No way.

69
00:04:21,094 --> 00:04:22,971
As a result, he was put in the spotlight

70
00:04:23,054 --> 00:04:25,431
-as the assailant of a sexual abuse case.
-Shit.

71
00:04:25,515 --> 00:04:27,475
The police, as they deemed the assailant…

72
00:04:27,976 --> 00:04:28,810
I see.

73
00:04:31,229 --> 00:04:33,523
But like I told you before,

74
00:04:33,606 --> 00:04:35,942
I have no say in that.

75
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:41,572
Yes, that would be an issue
with the procedure.

76
00:04:43,449 --> 00:04:45,034
Is that so?

77
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:46,911
What is it?

78
00:04:48,246 --> 00:04:49,539
All right.

79
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:53,584
I will relay your message
to our district office

80
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:55,795
and get back to you.

81
00:04:55,878 --> 00:04:56,796
Goodbye.

82
00:05:00,508 --> 00:05:01,968
What's the matter?

83
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:04,762
Sir.

84
00:05:09,434 --> 00:05:10,435
What is she doing?

85
00:05:11,019 --> 00:05:13,563
I don't know. She's in her room.

86
00:05:13,646 --> 00:05:15,732
What could she be doing in there all day?

87
00:05:15,815 --> 00:05:17,275
She even lost her phone.

88
00:05:17,358 --> 00:05:19,402
Just let her be. Yes.

89
00:05:19,485 --> 00:05:21,738
Call me if anything happens, okay?

90
00:05:21,821 --> 00:05:24,657
All right. See you tonight. Bye.

91
00:05:41,716 --> 00:05:44,552
It's illegal to have a paternity test
for an unborn baby, sir.

92
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:48,389
It's not impossible,

93
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:51,309
but it's too big of a risk
with the general election coming up.

94
00:05:55,271 --> 00:05:56,314
Let her stay here.

95
00:05:57,273 --> 00:05:58,691
That lowers the risk,

96
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:01,194
and she may be helpful to us.

97
00:06:03,071 --> 00:06:04,530
Not only did you lose Ji-hoon,

98
00:06:04,614 --> 00:06:07,492
but you took in his pregnant girlfriend
who had nowhere to stay.

99
00:06:08,951 --> 00:06:10,369
They'll feel your sincerity.

100
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:13,873
Woo-jae, that wasn't what I meant.

101
00:06:13,956 --> 00:06:14,916
I know, ma'am.

102
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:17,085
I understand.

103
00:06:17,919 --> 00:06:21,756
What I'm saying is that the girl
may seem like a ticking bomb,

104
00:06:22,507 --> 00:06:26,469
but she could actually be
a double-edged sword for us.

105
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,472
It was only a couple of days ago

106
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:31,974
that the Nation and People's Party
were on our case

107
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:34,852
about Ji-hoon's meth possession
and the favor from the police.

108
00:06:35,812 --> 00:06:37,271
The election is in seven months.

109
00:06:38,147 --> 00:06:41,484
If you kick her out now,
things could get out of control.

110
00:06:42,527 --> 00:06:44,362
You should be glad that she came to you.

111
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:47,490
Imagine if she had gone
to the opposing party instead.

112
00:06:48,491 --> 00:06:50,576
We don't know
her true intentions just yet,

113
00:06:51,494 --> 00:06:54,580
but you should keep her here

114
00:06:55,706 --> 00:06:57,834
and humor her for the time being.

115
00:07:01,295 --> 00:07:02,338
Sir.

116
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:05,174
You have to focus on the general election.

117
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:33,703
JICHEONG MIDDLE SCHOOL GRADUATION CEREMONY

118
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:52,847
Who was it that you had to
take the call outside?

119
00:07:52,930 --> 00:07:55,141
-Was it a guy?
-Don't be ridiculous.

120
00:07:55,224 --> 00:07:56,601
You still have a lot to do.

121
00:07:57,810 --> 00:07:59,103
Are you dizzy again?

122
00:07:59,770 --> 00:08:02,148
Sit down. Goodness.

123
00:08:05,985 --> 00:08:09,030
-Are you okay?
-Yes, I'm okay.

124
00:08:09,947 --> 00:08:12,700
You were doing better
after taking herbal medicine.

125
00:08:12,783 --> 00:08:15,745
I'll finish up making the dumplings.
Just go home and rest.

126
00:08:17,371 --> 00:08:20,208
I've already been clocking out early
despite being the owner.

127
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:22,585
-Now you want me to leave earlier?
-Yes.

128
00:08:24,378 --> 00:08:26,380
-Gosh.
-Do you want some water?

129
00:08:41,395 --> 00:08:42,271
Come in.

130
00:08:46,025 --> 00:08:47,318
What were you up to?

131
00:08:48,861 --> 00:08:49,904
Nothing.

132
00:08:50,947 --> 00:08:53,950
I need to go to work. This is your lunch.

133
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,409
Okay. Goodbye.

134
00:08:55,493 --> 00:08:59,580
Also, I thought you'd be bored
since you lost your phone.

135
00:08:59,664 --> 00:09:02,625
Yoon-seo and I enjoyed reading them,
but I'm not sure if you'll like them.

136
00:09:03,376 --> 00:09:05,086
Okay. I'll give them a try.

137
00:09:05,962 --> 00:09:07,547
Okay. I'll be back.

138
00:09:08,130 --> 00:09:09,090
Okay.

139
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:13,052
Take that girl to a hospital
and get her tested for drugs.

140
00:09:17,139 --> 00:09:18,432
Tomorrow, are you--

141
00:09:18,516 --> 00:09:21,477
Right. I'm going to the hospital later.

142
00:09:22,061 --> 00:09:24,772
I'm going to get that drug test.

143
00:09:25,815 --> 00:09:27,483
I gave it some thought.

144
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:30,069
I think it makes sense
that you and your husband

145
00:09:30,903 --> 00:09:31,904
have trouble trusting me.

146
00:09:32,697 --> 00:09:35,032
After all, Ji-hoon had bought drugs.

147
00:09:35,783 --> 00:09:37,410
Although he didn't use them.

148
00:09:38,369 --> 00:09:40,788
I swear that I'm clean as well.

149
00:09:40,871 --> 00:09:42,456
I'll prove it to you.

150
00:09:45,167 --> 00:09:47,295
Okay. Thanks.

151
00:09:47,378 --> 00:09:48,379
Don't mention it.

152
00:09:49,297 --> 00:09:51,757
Then I'll be out later today.

153
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:55,094
I'll go to work then.
I'll be back before dinnertime.

154
00:09:55,177 --> 00:09:56,429
Okay. Goodbye.

155
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:01,892
You know, that lid…

156
00:10:09,233 --> 00:10:11,819
BOOK CONSERVATION

157
00:10:15,823 --> 00:10:16,991
Come in.

158
00:10:31,922 --> 00:10:33,674
Everything looks so interesting here.

159
00:10:35,176 --> 00:10:36,594
I heard you fix books.

160
00:10:40,598 --> 00:10:42,224
Ji-hoon told me.

161
00:10:44,226 --> 00:10:46,729
-He told you that?
-Yes.

162
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:49,106
How do you fix books?

163
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:50,983
Well…

164
00:10:51,525 --> 00:10:54,278
I tend to say "conserve"
rather than "fix."

165
00:10:55,863 --> 00:10:57,448
What's the difference?

166
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:03,788
Take a seat and have a look.

167
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:10,002
ASSEMBLYMAN'S OFFICE

168
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:11,796
I'm sorry. Just a second.

169
00:11:17,468 --> 00:11:18,427
I reported it to him.

170
00:11:19,637 --> 00:11:20,513
Let's get to work.

171
00:11:21,097 --> 00:11:22,306
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

172
00:11:28,813 --> 00:11:30,147
Hello, this is Ko Min-seok.

173
00:11:30,731 --> 00:11:32,775
We'll contact you right away
once we're ready.

174
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:36,237
If it isn't Mr. Park Yeong-su.

175
00:11:37,655 --> 00:11:39,865
When are we going out for drinks?

176
00:11:39,949 --> 00:11:42,701
Are we strangers
just because I quit eight years ago?

177
00:11:45,996 --> 00:11:48,999
I know, why did he have to fall
in front of the kindergarten bus

178
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,334
and traumatize the kids?

179
00:11:51,627 --> 00:11:53,129
Assemblyman Nam's statement?

180
00:11:54,171 --> 00:11:55,756
We're still working on it.

181
00:11:56,632 --> 00:11:57,508
Yes.

182
00:11:58,426 --> 00:12:00,428
I'll send it over as soon as we're done.

183
00:12:02,346 --> 00:12:03,222
Okay.

184
00:12:04,265 --> 00:12:05,558
Goodbye.

185
00:12:08,394 --> 00:12:10,271
We'll need a draft of his statement.

186
00:12:10,354 --> 00:12:11,564
Sure.

187
00:12:16,277 --> 00:12:17,611
I'll be back in a bit.

188
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:18,654
-Okay.
-Okay.

189
00:12:20,072 --> 00:12:22,950
Assemblyman Nam Joong-do
of the Daehan Party

190
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:25,119
had mentioned him to the media recently.

191
00:12:25,202 --> 00:12:27,621
As a result, he was put in the spotlight

192
00:12:27,705 --> 00:12:29,623
as the assailant of a sexual abuse case.

193
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:38,007
Hello, ma'am.

194
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:41,302
Thank you so much for your time.

195
00:12:41,385 --> 00:12:43,095
Don't mention it.

196
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:46,348
I should be the one
thanking you for inviting me.

197
00:12:47,933 --> 00:12:51,270
She's put so much effort
into preparing for your visit

198
00:12:51,353 --> 00:12:53,939
over the past three months.

199
00:12:54,023 --> 00:12:56,775
And I've been losing sleep
for the past three months

200
00:12:56,859 --> 00:12:59,278
because I was so eager
to participate in this seminar.

201
00:13:00,571 --> 00:13:02,907
-Shall we go inside?
-Sure.

202
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:03,866
This way.

203
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:11,582
What's the matter?

204
00:13:13,584 --> 00:13:15,002
Ji Seung-kyu jumped off a building.

205
00:13:17,713 --> 00:13:19,131
He jumped off a building?

206
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:21,842
Ma'am, are you serious?

207
00:13:22,676 --> 00:13:26,597
That medical student committed suicide
by jumping off a building?

208
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:29,391
Yes, the articles
are being posted as we speak.

209
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:34,063
Come to think of it,
Assemblyman Nam was often referred to

210
00:13:34,146 --> 00:13:36,482
as Daehan Party's sharpshooter.

211
00:13:36,565 --> 00:13:39,527
But publicly attacking a mere civilian

212
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:43,531
and driving him to suicide?

213
00:13:44,156 --> 00:13:45,950
I'd say this is a terrible case of…

214
00:13:46,992 --> 00:13:49,745
improper handling of a firearm.

215
00:13:50,287 --> 00:13:51,747
You're absolutely right.

216
00:13:52,873 --> 00:13:53,999
Goodness.

217
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:56,585
JI SEUNG-KYU'S SUICIDE
SHARPSHOOTER NAM'S IMPROPER HANDLING

218
00:13:59,797 --> 00:14:01,840
Mr. Shin.

219
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:03,592
Yes, sir.

220
00:14:04,843 --> 00:14:08,305
Although there's nothing
we could possibly do to comfort

221
00:14:08,389 --> 00:14:10,766
the parents who lost
their child so tragically,

222
00:14:11,392 --> 00:14:13,852
find out where his wake is being held

223
00:14:13,936 --> 00:14:17,356
and send them some flowers under my name.

224
00:14:18,107 --> 00:14:19,024
Yes, sir.

225
00:14:22,278 --> 00:14:23,487
Goodness.

226
00:14:24,238 --> 00:14:26,282
I can't fathom
how Assemblyman Nam must feel.

227
00:14:26,782 --> 00:14:29,410
Anyway, we'll get going.

228
00:14:29,493 --> 00:14:31,537
-Please call me if anything happens.
-I will.

229
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:32,621
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

230
00:14:33,622 --> 00:14:34,540
Let's go.

231
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:47,011
FUNERAL HALL

232
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:00,024
No way.

233
00:15:01,442 --> 00:15:02,693
How is this possible?

234
00:15:05,195 --> 00:15:06,697
This is so fascinating.

235
00:15:09,825 --> 00:15:11,035
It's a totally different book.

236
00:15:14,079 --> 00:15:15,456
Do you think

237
00:15:16,123 --> 00:15:17,750
this could be done with people too?

238
00:15:18,834 --> 00:15:19,668
What?

239
00:15:23,881 --> 00:15:25,841
I was just asking.

240
00:15:28,469 --> 00:15:29,303
So…

241
00:15:30,804 --> 00:15:32,097
why did you bring me here?

242
00:15:32,723 --> 00:15:35,017
Right. Can you give me
that thing from earlier?

243
00:15:36,310 --> 00:15:37,227
Right.

244
00:16:00,626 --> 00:16:01,752
There.

245
00:16:04,004 --> 00:16:05,089
No way.

246
00:16:05,714 --> 00:16:06,757
Here you go.

247
00:16:07,341 --> 00:16:08,759
This must be a new lipstick.

248
00:16:10,886 --> 00:16:12,054
Someone gave it to me.

249
00:16:12,721 --> 00:16:15,140
And it's a lip balm, not lipstick.

250
00:16:16,058 --> 00:16:17,935
It's for moisturizing your lips.

251
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:20,312
I see.

252
00:16:20,396 --> 00:16:22,564
They make such great products these days.

253
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:24,566
It's a pretty color too. It suits you.

254
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:34,952
By the way, what's that?

255
00:16:36,996 --> 00:16:38,080
It's a dehumidifier.

256
00:16:39,415 --> 00:16:41,875
Since I work with paper,

257
00:16:41,959 --> 00:16:44,586
maintaining the right amount
of humidity is crucial.

258
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:46,922
It can't be too humid or dry here.

259
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:51,343
What if the weather
was fine during the day,

260
00:16:51,427 --> 00:16:53,762
but it starts to rain at night
when you're home?

261
00:16:54,763 --> 00:16:55,848
In that case…

262
00:16:57,683 --> 00:17:01,353
I can control it remotely
through the app on my phone.

263
00:17:02,855 --> 00:17:03,814
That's cool.

