526
00:35:39,554 --> 00:35:41,347
Hello, ma'am.

527
00:35:42,473 --> 00:35:43,558
Where are you headed?

528
00:35:44,559 --> 00:35:46,477
-To Youngsan.
-Sure thing.

529
00:35:47,812 --> 00:35:50,064
Wait. Youngsan?

530
00:35:50,148 --> 00:35:52,567
As in South Chungcheong-do?

531
00:35:53,693 --> 00:35:54,569
It's North.

532
00:35:55,236 --> 00:35:56,904
I see.

533
00:35:57,405 --> 00:36:00,158
That's really out of the way for me.

534
00:36:01,742 --> 00:36:03,202
I'll pay you for the round trip.

535
00:36:03,286 --> 00:36:05,746
Yes, ma'am. Hop in.

536
00:36:05,830 --> 00:36:07,165
Seung-hee.

537
00:36:10,877 --> 00:36:12,503
Hey, Ki-young.

538
00:36:23,097 --> 00:36:24,682
I didn't think you'd come.

539
00:36:31,355 --> 00:36:32,732
Is Mom home?

540
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:36,319
Your mother? Yes, she's there.

541
00:36:37,278 --> 00:36:39,363
I guess she's not out
shopping for land today.

542
00:36:40,364 --> 00:36:43,201
Of course not.
She's waiting for you at home.

543
00:36:47,538 --> 00:36:48,748
You don't need to lie.

544
00:36:49,707 --> 00:36:53,252
Why would she wait for me
when I ran off for three years

545
00:36:53,878 --> 00:36:55,796
saying that I couldn't stand her?

546
00:37:11,938 --> 00:37:13,189
MED STUDENT COMMITS SUICIDE

547
00:37:15,274 --> 00:37:18,527
ASSEMBLYMAN NAM'S PLEA
FOR A REINVESTIGATION DROVE HIM TO SUICIDE

548
00:37:30,790 --> 00:37:32,708
LEE SEUL-GI MEDICAL CLINIC

549
00:37:40,383 --> 00:37:43,844
LEE SEUL-GI MEDICAL CLINIC

550
00:37:50,226 --> 00:37:52,103
-I'd like to take a drug test.
-Pardon?

551
00:37:54,981 --> 00:37:56,148
A drug test.

552
00:37:57,024 --> 00:37:58,401
The medical student's wake?

553
00:37:59,110 --> 00:38:00,194
Why would you go there?

554
00:38:00,278 --> 00:38:02,989
It's bothering me too much.

555
00:38:03,072 --> 00:38:06,784
Hye-joo, I understand
that this was unexpected

556
00:38:06,867 --> 00:38:08,494
and that you're feeling troubled.

557
00:38:08,577 --> 00:38:11,038
But no one is criticizing
Joong-do right now.

558
00:38:11,622 --> 00:38:13,624
I'm not saying they're right,

559
00:38:13,708 --> 00:38:16,502
but people are saying
that the kid deserved it.

560
00:38:17,169 --> 00:38:19,046
I doubt Joong-do will go there.

561
00:38:19,630 --> 00:38:22,133
If he does, it may seem like
he's taking responsibility

562
00:38:22,216 --> 00:38:24,093
for that kid's death.

563
00:38:24,635 --> 00:38:26,595
But that's not the case.

564
00:38:26,679 --> 00:38:30,224
So you shouldn't go there either. Okay?

565
00:38:30,891 --> 00:38:33,602
Think of what the bereaved family
might say to you.

566
00:38:33,686 --> 00:38:34,729
Okay.

567
00:38:35,980 --> 00:38:37,315
I'll see you later.

568
00:38:38,107 --> 00:38:38,941
Okay.

569
00:38:40,401 --> 00:38:41,444
Bye.

570
00:38:48,617 --> 00:38:49,618
Get out!

571
00:38:50,119 --> 00:38:52,204
How dare you come here?

572
00:38:52,288 --> 00:38:53,539
Get out!

573
00:38:54,498 --> 00:38:56,917
How dare you set foot in here?

574
00:38:58,586 --> 00:39:00,212
How brazen could you be?

575
00:39:12,683 --> 00:39:13,768
YOUNGSAN SESAME OIL

576
00:39:13,851 --> 00:39:14,810
Youngsan.

577
00:39:14,894 --> 00:39:16,312
You know where that is, right?

578
00:39:17,021 --> 00:39:18,606
In North Chungcheong-do.

579
00:39:18,689 --> 00:39:20,358
Take them.

580
00:39:20,441 --> 00:39:22,985
-No, it's okay.
-Just take them.

581
00:39:23,069 --> 00:39:25,029
Take this. Okay?

582
00:39:48,511 --> 00:39:49,470
We've arrived, sir.

583
00:39:50,471 --> 00:39:51,680
Thank you.

584
00:39:51,764 --> 00:39:53,099
Let's go.

585
00:39:56,185 --> 00:39:57,395
-Hello.
-Hello.

586
00:39:59,522 --> 00:40:00,981
Nam Joong-do, you bastard!

587
00:40:01,065 --> 00:40:03,109
You killed my child
and won't even come to his wake.

588
00:40:03,192 --> 00:40:05,027
How can you call yourself human?

589
00:40:05,111 --> 00:40:07,530
-Nam Joong-do! Do you know who I am?
-Stop him.

590
00:40:08,364 --> 00:40:11,200
I'm Ji Seung-kyu's father!
The father of the boy you killed!

591
00:40:11,283 --> 00:40:12,576
-Stop it!
-Get inside, sir!

592
00:40:12,660 --> 00:40:15,121
-Let me go!
-You murderer!

593
00:40:15,955 --> 00:40:19,458
You killed our son!

594
00:40:21,502 --> 00:40:22,878
Nam Joong-do, you murderer!

595
00:40:28,801 --> 00:40:31,387
Murderer!

596
00:40:31,470 --> 00:40:33,514
Where are you going, you bastard?

597
00:40:34,473 --> 00:40:36,142
Are you okay?

598
00:40:36,225 --> 00:40:37,643
I can't believe this.

599
00:40:37,726 --> 00:40:39,186
Use this.

600
00:41:11,218 --> 00:41:14,346
I'd like to thank you
for your interest in paternity leave

601
00:41:14,430 --> 00:41:19,435
and for attending this debate
held in support of this policy.

602
00:41:20,019 --> 00:41:22,855
Paternity leave is a right

603
00:41:22,938 --> 00:41:25,149
for all infants and their parents.

604
00:41:25,733 --> 00:41:27,985
Frankly, I never took paternity leave.

605
00:41:28,694 --> 00:41:30,988
If my wife finds out
that I'm giving a speech here,

606
00:41:31,071 --> 00:41:32,823
she'll give me an earful.

607
00:41:33,741 --> 00:41:37,703
So please keep this a secret from her.

608
00:41:38,287 --> 00:41:39,246
Okay.

609
00:41:39,330 --> 00:41:40,498
PML is an abbreviation

610
00:41:40,581 --> 00:41:43,417
for "pregnancy and maternity leave."

611
00:41:54,136 --> 00:41:55,387
Hey.

612
00:41:56,430 --> 00:41:57,765
-Hey.
-Sorry for being late.

613
00:41:57,848 --> 00:41:59,475
That's okay. Did you eat?

614
00:41:59,558 --> 00:42:00,768
Of course not.

615
00:42:11,153 --> 00:42:12,947
MS. KIM

616
00:42:31,340 --> 00:42:32,424
Ms. Kim.

617
00:42:36,345 --> 00:42:37,513
It's me, Soo-bin.

618
00:42:52,444 --> 00:42:54,530
Why didn't you go home?

619
00:42:56,365 --> 00:42:57,199
I was bored.

620
00:43:00,035 --> 00:43:02,496
Can I come in and watch you work?

621
00:43:10,170 --> 00:43:11,380
Thank you, sir.

622
00:43:11,463 --> 00:43:12,548
My pleasure.

623
00:43:12,631 --> 00:43:13,924
I loved your speech.

624
00:43:14,008 --> 00:43:15,217
Thank you.

625
00:43:15,801 --> 00:43:16,969
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

626
00:43:17,886 --> 00:43:19,763
-Good work.
-Thank you.

627
00:43:40,576 --> 00:43:42,536
-Thanks for the jacket.
-Don't mention it.

628
00:43:44,204 --> 00:43:45,873
The rest of your schedule
is at the National Assembly.

629
00:43:45,956 --> 00:43:47,625
You can wear the spare suit in your--

630
00:43:47,708 --> 00:43:48,959
Wait.

631
00:43:50,836 --> 00:43:53,464
I'm sorry, but could you cancel
my schedule for the day?

632
00:43:55,090 --> 00:43:58,302
Mr. Park, you can go home
after dropping me off here.

633
00:43:59,887 --> 00:44:00,721
Yes, sir.

634
00:44:09,647 --> 00:44:11,815
Are you going somewhere?
We can drive you there.

635
00:44:12,566 --> 00:44:15,027
That's okay. Could you take
my suit to a dry cleaner?

636
00:44:16,820 --> 00:44:18,197
I'm sorry. See you tomorrow.

637
00:44:46,642 --> 00:44:47,643
By the way,

638
00:44:48,811 --> 00:44:52,398
do you have to graduate from university
to become a book conservator?

639
00:44:53,273 --> 00:44:55,025
I didn't go to university.

640
00:44:56,735 --> 00:44:59,071
-Really?
-Yes.

641
00:44:59,154 --> 00:45:00,155
I see.

642
00:45:00,239 --> 00:45:01,156
Right.

643
00:45:01,740 --> 00:45:03,534
I think Ji-hoon mentioned that.

644
00:45:07,496 --> 00:45:10,582
He told you that?

645
00:45:11,166 --> 00:45:12,126
Yes.

646
00:45:15,170 --> 00:45:18,090
I don't have any parents. Just like you.

647
00:45:20,551 --> 00:45:22,344
Ji-hoon told me.

648
00:45:26,682 --> 00:45:28,058
Did he tell you anything else?

649
00:45:28,142 --> 00:45:32,229
Did Ji-hoon tell you
anything else about me?

650
00:45:41,113 --> 00:45:41,989
He did.

651
00:45:47,536 --> 00:45:49,788
That you're not his birth mother.

652
00:45:55,085 --> 00:45:56,003
Anything else?

653
00:45:58,297 --> 00:45:59,131
No.

654
00:46:00,048 --> 00:46:00,924
That's all.

655
00:46:12,978 --> 00:46:13,979
I'm sorry, Soo-bin,

656
00:46:14,062 --> 00:46:16,565
but could you go
and buy me a bottle of water?

657
00:46:17,858 --> 00:46:18,775
Water?

658
00:46:18,859 --> 00:46:22,029
Do you remember seeing
a convenience store nearby?

659
00:46:22,112 --> 00:46:23,489
Can you get me one from there?

660
00:46:24,072 --> 00:46:25,991
I forgot to buy it.

661
00:46:27,826 --> 00:46:28,994
Sure.

662
00:46:29,077 --> 00:46:32,247
My purse is in my handbag. Take it.

663
00:46:32,331 --> 00:46:33,874
I have enough money for water.

664
00:46:35,125 --> 00:46:36,126
I'll be back.

665
00:46:54,019 --> 00:46:56,188
That you're not his birth mother.

666
00:46:57,356 --> 00:46:58,565
That's all.

667
00:47:06,573 --> 00:47:08,492
What did you expect?

668
00:47:21,421 --> 00:47:23,298
Mom, I'm home.

669
00:47:24,675 --> 00:47:25,801
You came together.

670
00:47:26,969 --> 00:47:30,055
Yes, I picked her up from the airport.

671
00:47:30,138 --> 00:47:32,766
Why didn't you just leave
while you were at the airport?

672
00:47:32,849 --> 00:47:34,101
Why did you come back?

673
00:47:36,812 --> 00:47:37,688
Come on, Mom.

674
00:47:38,939 --> 00:47:40,274
Don't be like that.

675
00:47:40,357 --> 00:47:42,317
Didn't you miss me? It's been three years.

676
00:47:43,360 --> 00:47:45,821
Why would I miss the daughter
who abandoned me?

677
00:48:20,647 --> 00:48:21,898
Honey.

678
00:48:25,569 --> 00:48:26,445
Hye-joo.

679
00:48:38,707 --> 00:48:40,250
This is just too hard.

680
00:48:49,801 --> 00:48:51,053
Someone died…

681
00:48:55,307 --> 00:48:56,642
because of me.

682
00:49:05,400 --> 00:49:06,360
No.

683
00:49:07,277 --> 00:49:08,904
It wasn't your fault.

684
00:49:08,987 --> 00:49:12,366
You didn't do anything wrong.
You're not to blame, honey.

685
00:49:13,492 --> 00:49:15,786
You didn't know this would happen.

686
00:49:17,412 --> 00:49:18,455
But…

687
00:49:22,084 --> 00:49:24,378
But they lost their son

688
00:49:25,629 --> 00:49:26,838
because of me.

689
00:49:32,177 --> 00:49:35,472
Ever since I fell in love with him,

690
00:49:37,140 --> 00:49:38,100
I…

691
00:49:39,476 --> 00:49:41,269
I know exactly how that feels.

692
00:49:42,479 --> 00:49:46,441
…have never once doubted…

693
00:49:46,525 --> 00:49:47,526
It's all my fault.

694
00:49:48,318 --> 00:49:49,569
…the kind heart he has…

695
00:49:50,487 --> 00:49:51,947
They lost their son.

696
00:49:53,949 --> 00:49:55,534
…toward this world

697
00:49:56,618 --> 00:49:58,328
-that we lived in.
-I'm here.

698
00:49:58,412 --> 00:49:59,830
-Have some of this.
-Not once.

699
00:50:00,997 --> 00:50:02,124
Hey.

700
00:50:02,207 --> 00:50:03,041
Come sit.

701
00:50:03,542 --> 00:50:04,418
Come on.

702
00:50:11,299 --> 00:50:12,676
Stay a bit longer.

703
00:50:13,385 --> 00:50:16,304
-We can eat together.
-That's okay.

704
00:50:16,388 --> 00:50:18,849
You should save it for tomorrow.

705
00:50:18,932 --> 00:50:20,517
Don't worry about tomorrow.

706
00:50:21,184 --> 00:50:22,018
I'll be back.

707
00:50:22,811 --> 00:50:24,563
Enjoy your meal. Goodbye.

708
00:50:24,646 --> 00:50:26,022
-Are you sure?
-Yes.

709
00:50:26,106 --> 00:50:27,274
-Come by again.
-I will.

710
00:50:32,654 --> 00:50:34,489
-Goodbye.
-Go home safely.

711
00:50:34,573 --> 00:50:35,532
-Okay.
-Go on.

712
00:50:38,368 --> 00:50:40,662
Goodbye. Go home safely.

713
00:50:40,746 --> 00:50:41,997
-Okay.
-Bye.

714
00:50:42,998 --> 00:50:45,834
HAJEONG-DONG, SINYANG-GU

715
00:50:47,836 --> 00:50:49,921
She must work at the community center.

716
00:50:50,005 --> 00:50:51,047
No.

717
00:50:51,548 --> 00:50:54,009
I asked her and she said she didn't.

718
00:50:56,428 --> 00:50:57,471
Then where?

719
00:50:58,013 --> 00:51:00,015
I'm not sure. I don't even know her name.

720
00:51:00,599 --> 00:51:01,892
She won't tell me.

721
00:51:02,476 --> 00:51:05,228
But you haven't told me
where you're from either, young man.

722
00:51:07,773 --> 00:51:08,815
I'm not that young.

723
00:51:08,899 --> 00:51:10,817
Goodness. Are you married?

724
00:51:10,901 --> 00:51:13,111
You look so young.

725
00:51:13,195 --> 00:51:14,237
I have a child.

726
00:51:15,197 --> 00:51:17,908
-A child?
-Ma'am, the stew is getting cold.

727
00:51:17,991 --> 00:51:19,493
-Let's eat.
-Okay.

728
00:51:48,814 --> 00:51:50,565
It's been three years now.

729
00:51:51,107 --> 00:51:52,734
Who could it be?

730
00:51:52,818 --> 00:51:54,861
They sent us a hefty sum.

731
00:51:54,945 --> 00:51:55,821
Exactly.

732
00:51:55,904 --> 00:51:59,533
-And it's anonymous, so they'll be taxed.
-Did the Anonymous Angel come by again?

733
00:51:59,616 --> 00:52:03,370
Yes. Along with a million won,
just like the other times.

734
00:52:03,453 --> 00:52:04,913
Let me help.

735
00:52:04,996 --> 00:52:06,456
-Let's put it on the cart.
-Okay.

736
00:52:06,957 --> 00:52:08,083
-One, two…
-One, two…

737
00:52:14,631 --> 00:52:17,592
I fixed it,
so it should last you a bit longer.

738
00:52:17,676 --> 00:52:20,887
Goodness, thank you.
You're better than my own kids.

739
00:52:29,855 --> 00:52:31,356
-I'll get going.
-Hold on.

740
00:52:33,233 --> 00:52:34,276
Here.

741
00:52:34,359 --> 00:52:36,194
-Thank you.
-Go on.

742
00:52:36,278 --> 00:52:37,362
Goodbye.

743
00:52:43,869 --> 00:52:45,745
Goodness. You're here.

744
00:52:45,829 --> 00:52:47,455
Hello. Have you been well?

745
00:52:48,039 --> 00:52:49,291
Have some apples.

746
00:52:49,374 --> 00:52:50,625
Okay.

747
00:53:37,797 --> 00:53:39,633
SINYANG-GU SENIOR WELFARE CENTER

748
00:54:01,154 --> 00:54:02,155
Ma'am.

749
00:54:02,656 --> 00:54:03,782
Ma'am, the meat--

750
00:54:11,790 --> 00:54:13,249
You're here.

751
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:15,460
-Hello.
-Goodness.

752
00:54:26,721 --> 00:54:28,390
-Eat up.
-Okay.

753
00:54:30,225 --> 00:54:31,226
Thank you.

754
00:54:32,394 --> 00:54:34,813
I'll get you some rice tea.

755
00:54:34,896 --> 00:54:35,814
Let me.

756
00:54:35,897 --> 00:54:39,484
It's okay. You two stay and eat.
I'll go get it.

757
00:54:39,567 --> 00:54:40,735
Sit down.

758
00:54:40,819 --> 00:54:41,695
Come on.

759
00:55:02,716 --> 00:55:04,926
About that rice…

760
00:55:06,594 --> 00:55:09,723
I didn't tell anyone, so don't worry.

761
00:55:11,433 --> 00:55:12,392
Thank you.

762
00:55:25,655 --> 00:55:28,783
My name is Nam Joong-do.

763
00:55:28,867 --> 00:55:29,826
What's your name?

764
00:55:29,909 --> 00:55:31,119
I'm Hye-joo.

765
00:55:32,328 --> 00:55:33,496
Kim Hye-joo.

766
00:55:35,290 --> 00:55:36,666
Ms. Kim Hye-joo.

767
00:55:38,126 --> 00:55:38,960
How pretty.

768
00:55:41,838 --> 00:55:45,050
I meant your name. You have a pretty name.

769
00:56:22,378 --> 00:56:23,296
My child died

770
00:56:24,714 --> 00:56:26,341
because of you.

771
00:56:30,261 --> 00:56:31,221
Get out!

772
00:56:31,805 --> 00:56:33,348
How dare you come here?

773
00:56:33,932 --> 00:56:35,266
Get out of here this instant!

774
00:56:35,350 --> 00:56:36,267
Get out!

775
00:56:37,477 --> 00:56:39,771
How dare you set foot in here?

776
00:56:45,527 --> 00:56:48,363
Mom, I'm hungry. Let's eat.

777
00:56:48,446 --> 00:56:51,116
-I don't want to.
-We haven't eaten together in a while.

778
00:56:51,199 --> 00:56:53,952
Why are you being so friendly? Let me go.

779
00:56:54,035 --> 00:56:56,871
-Mom.
-Did you forget that you left me?

780
00:57:20,436 --> 00:57:21,479
Will you have the baby?

781
00:57:24,899 --> 00:57:27,360
I'm not sure. Would you prefer that?

782
00:57:30,155 --> 00:57:32,782
I guess that depends on who the father is.

783
00:57:35,535 --> 00:57:37,245
Ji-hoon might not be the father.

784
00:57:42,917 --> 00:57:43,960
You're right.

785
00:57:44,961 --> 00:57:46,629
He might not be.

786
00:58:04,314 --> 00:58:11,070
I LOVE YOU, MOM AND DAD.
SINCERELY, NAM JI-HOON

787
00:58:32,300 --> 00:58:34,844
TROLLEY

788
00:58:34,928 --> 00:58:38,723
You know that I gave you up
to share with the world, right?

789
00:58:38,806 --> 00:58:40,266
I just want to be here with you.

790
00:58:40,350 --> 00:58:43,144
I came by to see you,
so I'll just be doing that.

791
00:58:43,228 --> 00:58:44,771
Are you going to stay in that house?

792
00:58:44,854 --> 00:58:46,397
Then lay low, as if you're dead.

793
00:58:46,481 --> 00:58:47,899
Don't get too attached to her.

794
00:58:47,982 --> 00:58:49,442
I'm afraid you'll get hurt.

795
00:58:49,526 --> 00:58:50,568
I got tested for drugs.

796
00:58:50,652 --> 00:58:53,655
I don't know what to feel
whenever I see her.

797
00:58:53,738 --> 00:58:56,533
Frankly, I'm very disappointed
in your wife.

798
00:58:56,616 --> 00:58:58,284
Youngsan? Why all of a sudden?

799
00:58:58,368 --> 00:59:00,954
It's your hometown,
so I was wondering if you knew anyone.

800
00:59:01,538 --> 00:59:02,872
If you had to choose

801
00:59:02,956 --> 00:59:05,959
between the world you dream of
and your wife,

802
00:59:06,042 --> 00:59:07,794
which one would you choose?

